Michelle Pittman

Michelle Pittman

Board & Office Coordinator

Michelle serves as the initial point of contact for prospective homeowners and is the primary contact for families who are being developed in the buyer pool development program.  She assists in the coordination of the Soft Second Mortgage Program. Michelle has been in this position since 2013 and served as Asset Management Assistant and Homeownership Coordinator from 2011-2013.  Michelle also serves as the organization’s Executive Administrator where she is responsible for coordination of all board of directors activities, managing special projects, handling routine office duties and providing support for the CEO. Prior to Providence, Michelle was employed with American Nursing Services for twelve years coordinating homecare services and quality management. She is a graduate of the University of New Orleans with a Bachelor of Arts in Sociology.

My self-summary
Hey there. My name is James. I'm a lover and a fighter, a painter, a porn vendor, a would-be philanthropist, a home-body, and am perpetually reinventing myself.

I like sociopolitical documentaries, long walks on the beach, and pondering solutions to world issues.
What I’m doing with my life
At the moment I work part-time at the love shop, and am in the midst of starting up a web-cam show.

My goals in my life are to speak at least 5 languages fluently, and to learn computer programming and build robots/drones/3D-printers and solve many of the world's problems with them. I'm working steadily towards both goals!
I’m really good at
Languages are kinda my thing. I studied linguistics at U of T for a year, and I tend to pick up languages really fast. I know bits and pieces of many tongues.

I'm also a bit of a technology buff. I'm into gadgetry and gizmos, and can probably tell what phone you have at first glance.
The first things people usually notice about me
I'm pretty tall. That's usually the first comment. Haha
Favorite books, movies, shows, music, and food
I'm really into the Game of Thrones books/show right now. Apart from that I'm not really caught up in anything. Seen some of the current season of big brother because my friends force me to watch, haha. Kenny is a fox!
Six things I could never do without
My phone, hot showers, the internet, cake, long drives, and hugs
I spend a lot of time thinking about
What the major problems are with the world are, and how I can personally fix them. Lol
On a typical Friday night I am
Reading and baking cookies.
You should message me if
You don't bore easy. I tend to ramble about things you won't care about. Haha!

My Groups

Jan B

Jan is one of the wonderful volunteers that run the Kelmscott Show. Jan first started volunteering at the show after seeing a sign about volunteering at the show.  Believe it or not her first role was a 'post'. This important role was to assist the Ground Space Coordinator and her mark-up crew. Jan felt she made a great post! 

The following year Jan coordinated the River Market at the Kelmscott Show. The market went well and Jan was ready for a new challenge. Jan took on the role of Show Secretary and found she really enjoyed the role. It can be quite busy but Jan gets to complete lots of interesting tasks. 

Jan has just completed her third Kelmscott Show.

Thanks Jan!

Meet Wilfredo & Jeanne A video message from Wilfredo & Jeanne Call or Text us Send a message A Letter from Wilfredo & Jeanne ¡Hola! We are Wilfredo and Jeanne, and we are so excited to grow our family again through adoption. Love and laughter overflow from our home and farm here in Maryland. Thank you for taking a moment to get to know us. We are praying for you and for this adoption journey we are both on. Our Story We have been married for 12 years and have always dreamed of having a big family yet, after a few years, we learned that we could not conceive.  We came to see that God had another plan for our family, adoption. 5 years ago, we were blessed to adopt our daughter Isabel, and now we are excited to grow our family again through adoption. We speak Spanish and English at home and Isabel is learning both.  We are Catholic and active in our faith, striving to let God’s love and light shine through us. We love working on our mini farm together as a family.  Every time we try to scale it back, we seem to plant more.  Corn, tomatoes, peas, radishes, green beans, peppers, and cucumbers are some favorites! We have chickens who share silly antics as well as lots of fresh eggs.  A year ago, we added sheep to the mix, and we love them. When we are not playing farm, we love to sing silly songs, play games, grill or cook together, do craft projects, visit with friends, and enjoy each other’s company. About Wilfredo Wilfredo is a truly kind and generous man, completely committed as a husband and a father. A hard-working provider, he is dedicated to our family. If you are in need, this is the man you want by your side – he would persevere through any difficulty but make you laugh all the while. Wilfredo runs his own landscaping business. In his free time, you can find him fishing, hiking, grilling, or even occasionally resting in our hammock. Wilfredo is a fantastic father and has so much love to share with our daughter. I look forward to watching him sharing his love with another child, as he teaches through farm chores or makes up silly games with another child/children. About Jeanne Jeanne loves being a mom, and all that goes with it. She enjoys cooking and even doing laundry but does not mind when she gets a break from doing dishes. Jeanne is a stay-at-home mom but does help out a few hours a week in the home office of our family business. Jeanne is quiet and thoughtful, with a silly sense of humor and ready to help anyone in need. She loves to be outside- especially in our garden.  When she is enjoying downtime, you can often find her reading a book or catching up with old friends. Jeanne is so excited to think of her family growing, and dreams of sharing love, snuggles, stories, and songs with a new child/children. Our Daughter Isabel Isabel radiates laughter and energy wherever she goes. She adores her lambies and takes good care of our baby chicks. Isabel is beyond excited at the idea of being a big sister and would be so proud to help Mama with any new children we were blessed with. Our Family We have a large, loving, and excited extended family, living both nearby and in El Salvador. Wilfredo is the oldest of 5 and Jeanne of 3 and there are aunts, uncles, and cousins of every age and variety. They are all crazy about Isabel and excited for our family to grow again through adoption. Our Home in Maryland We live on about 8 acres in a rural pocket of Maryland, close enough to the city to be able to explore when we desire yet otherwise out in the country. Our home has three bedrooms and is perfectly cozy. We love sharing meals by our woodstove in the winter months and curling up on the sofa with a good book. Most of the time, you will find us outside. Our yard, barns, and gardens offer lots of outdoor spaces for work and play and the nearby river and parks give us even more areas for adventure. Our Promise to You We promise that your child will know unconditional love and support throughout life. We promise to raise your child or children in Faith so that he or she grows to one day be a trustworthy man or woman of integrity and compassion. We are happy to be in touch with you as you feel most comfortable, whether that is photos, letters, messages, or visits. We promise that your child will know his or her story and will know the love and grace of this adoption journey. To learn more about us, please call or text Lifetime at 1.800.923.6784. Learn More About Wilfredo & Jeanne   Wilfredo Jeanne Our EducationHigh School in El SalvadorMasters in Social Work Our ProfessionsLandscape Owner/OperatorStay at home mom/ Part time at family business Our Racial BackgroundHispanicCaucasian Some of Wilfredo & Jeanne's Favorites Thing to grow in the garden:Corn – a traditional variety from El Salvador I have been perfecting for Maryland weatherSweet Potatoes – the vines are so green and beautiful and grow well with very little fussing from me Animal to raise:Cows – we don’t have any yet but that is next on the listTurkeys – they are totally goofy Place to visit:El Salvador – there is nowhere quite like the place you grow upEl Salvador – family is family Food:SeafoodChocolate - that’s a food group, right? Quote:“I must be willing to give whatever it takes to do good to others. This requires that I be willing to give until it hurts. Otherwise, there is no true love in me, and I bring injustice, not peace, to those around me.” ― St. Mother Teresa of Calcutta“Perfect love drives out fear” ― 1 John 4:18 I want to teach my child…To have faith, to be strong, to believe in their self but to believe in God firstTo love and be loved. Time of Year:SpringEaster – the beauty of the season springs forth in all Creation More About Our Family Our Faith We were both raised Catholic, met at Mass, and have shared our love for the Faith ever since We live in the state of Our Home Small but cozy, sunny and warm – we have three bedrooms all on one floor with the kitchen and living room; Our second floor is an unfinished attic we use for storage; Our basement is half unfinished and half home office for our business. Our Surroundings Out in the country with lots of space to play and to garden. There is a river nearby with lots of parks along it to explore. Baltimore and Washington are both within easy driving distances for work and adventure. Family Activities Impromptu dance parties, picking vegetables, giving the sheep a bath, craft projects, chatting around a bonfire and grilling, collecting our chicken eggs, tilling the garden, hiking, swimming and fishing at the river. Food Interests Homemade tortillas, canning tomatoes, pickling vegetables (cabbage is a surprise family favorite), making soups and broths, and new ways to use lots of fresh eggs. We Prefer a Child Who Is... Age of Child Newborn to 3 years old. We would love twins Either or Both Sibling Group Definitely, with the oldest up to three years of age. Ethnicity of ChildCaucasian, Hispanic, Asian, Hispanic/African American, Hispanic/Caucasian, Hispanic/Other, Asian/Caucasian, African American/Caucasian, Native American, Native American/Caucasian, East Indian Future Contact with Birth Family We would be happy to share updates, photos, and visits to the extent that is comfortable for you. In Closing Thank you for taking some time to get to know a bit about us. We would love to hear from you! Please contact us through Lifetime Adoption at 1-800-923-6784.
